===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|弓|彡|ls=ic|t1=bow|t2=hair, meaning "decoration" in this case}}—a decorative bow that is functionally inferior. Or it might be indicating that the bow is shaking, which implies a worn-out bow. 

An alternate etymology is 𢎥 + 𢎥, 𢎥 being a variant of 卷.

===Etymology 1===
Probably cognate with {{och-l|柔|soft}}, see there for more (STEDT).

{{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007; p. 448)}} and {{zh-ref|Hill (2019; p. 21)}} compare this word to {{cog|bo|ཉོག་ཉོང|t=soft, weak}}. Hill also adds {{cog|my|ညက်|t=to be smooth}} to the comparison. From this, one can reconstruct {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*njewk}}.

